obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (4089)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4089&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Water (Prevention`
  line `and Control of Pollution) Act, 1974.`
  line
  line `(2) It applies in the first instance to the whole of the States of Assam, Bihar, Gujarat, Haryana,`
  line `Himachal Pradesh, Jammu and Kashmir, Karnataka, Kerala, Madhya Pradesh, Rajasthan, Tripura and`
  line `West Bengal and the Union territories; and it shall apply to such other State which adopts this Act by`
  line `resolution passed in that behalf under clause (1) of article 252 of the Constitution.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force, at once in the States of Assam, Bihar, Gujarat, Haryana, Himachal`
  line `Pradesh, Jammu and Kashmir, Karnataka, Kerala, Madhya Pradesh, Rajasthan, Tripura and West Bengal`
  line `and in the Union territories, and in any other State which adopts this Act under clause (1) of article 252 of`
  line `the Constitution on the date of such adoption and any reference in this Act to the commencement of this`
  line `Act shall, in relation to any State or Union territory, mean the date on which this Act comes into force in`
  line `such State or Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (4090)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4090&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Board" means the Central Board or a State Board;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(b) "Central Board" means the Central Pollution Control Board constituted under section 3;]`
  line
  line `(c) "member" means a member of a Board and includes the chairman thereof;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(d) "occupier", in relation to any factory or premises, means the person who has control over the`
  line `affairs of the factory or the premises, and includes, in relation to any substance, the person in`
  line `possession of the substance;]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(dd) "outlet" includes any conduit pipe or channel, open or closed, carrying sewage or trade`
  line `effluent or any other holding arrangement which causes, or is likely to cause, pollution;]`
  line
  line `(e) "pollution" means such contamination of water or such alteration of the physical, chemical or`
  line `biological properties of water or such discharge of any sewage or trade effluent or of any other liquid,`
  line `gaseous or solid substance into water (whether directly or indirectly) as may, or is likely to, create a`
  line `nuisance or render such water harmful or injurious to public health or safety, or to domestic,`
  line `commercial, industrial, agricultural or other legitimate uses, or to the life and health of animals or`
  line `plants or of acquatic organisms;`
  line
  line `(f) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act by the Central Government or, as`
  line `the case may be, the State Government;`
  line
  line `(g) "sewage effluent" means effluent from any sewerage system or sewage disposal works and`
  line `includes sullage from open drains;`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(gg) "sewer" means any conduit pipe or channel, open or closed, carrying sewage or trade`
  line effluent;]
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(h) "State Board" means a State Pollution Control Board constituted under section 4;]`
  line
  line `(i) "State Government" in relation to a Union territory means the Administrator thereof`
  line `appointed under article 239 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(j) "stream" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) river;`
  line
  line `(ii) water course (whether flowing or for the time being dry);`
  line
  line `(iii) inland water (whether natural or artificial);`
  line
  line `(iv) sub-terranean waters;`
  line
  line `(v) sea or tidal waters to such extent or, as the case may be, to such point as the State`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(k) "trade effluent" includes any liquid, gaseous or solid substance which is discharged from any`
  line `premises used for carrying on any ^5`
  line `[industry, operation or process, or treatment and disposal system],`
  line `other than domestic sewage.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 2, for clause (b) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (d) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 2, for clause (h) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for "trade or industry" (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (4091)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of Central Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4091&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, with effect from such date`
  line `(being a date not later than six months of the commencement of this Act in the States of Assam, Bihar,`
  line `Gujarat, Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Jammu and Kashmir, Karnataka, Kerala, Madhya Pradesh,`
  line `Rajasthan, Tripura and West Bengal and in the Union territories) as it may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint, constitute a Central Board to be called the ^1`
  line `[Central Pollution Control Board] to exercise`
  line `the powers conferred on and perform the functions assigned to that Board under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a full-time chairman, being a person having special knowledge or practical experience in`
  line `respect of ^2`
  line `[matters relating to environmental protection] or a person having knowledge and`
  line `experience in administering institutions dealing with the matters aforesaid, to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b)`
  line ^3
  line `[such number of officials, not exceeding five,] to be nominated by the Central Government to`
  line `represent that Government;`
  line
  line `(c) such number of persons, not exceeding five, to be nominated by the Central Government,`
  line `from amongst the members of the State Boards, of whom not exceeding two shall be from those`
  line `referred to in clause (c) of sub-section (2) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d)`
  line ^4
  line `[such number of non-officials, not exceeding three,] to be nominated by the Central`
  line `Government, to represent the interests of agriculture, fishery or industry or trade or any other interest`
  line `which, in the opinion of the Central Government, ought to be represented;`
  line
  line `(e) two persons to represent the companies or corporations owned, controlled or managed by the`
  line `Central Government, to be nominated by that Government;`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(f) a full-time member-secretary, possessing qualifications, knowledge and experience of`
  line `scientific, engineering or management aspects of pollution control, to be appointed by the Central`
  line Government.]
  line
  line `(3) The Central Board shall be a body corporate with the name aforesaid having perpetual succession`
  line `and a common seal with power, subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of`
  line `property and to contract, and may, by the aforesaid name, sue or be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Central Board for the Prevention and Control of Water Pollution" (w.e.f. 29-91988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 3, for "matters relating to the use and conservation of water resources or the prevention and control`
  line `of water pollution" (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 3, for "five officials" (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "three non-officials" (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 3, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (4092)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Constitution of State Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4092&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government shall, with effect from such date ^1`
  line `*** as`
  line `it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, constitute a ^2`
  line `[State Pollution Control Board],`
  line `under such name as may be specified in the notification, to exercise the powers conferred on and perform`
  line `the functions assigned to that Board under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A State Board shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a ^3*** chairman, being a person having special knowledge or practical experience in respect of ^4[matters relating to environmental protection] or a person having knowledge and experience in administering institutions dealing with the matters aforesaid, to be nominated by the State Government ^5[in such manner as may be prescribed by the central Government]:br`
  line
  line `^6[Provided that the chairman may be either whole-time or part-time as the State Government may may think fit;]`
  line
  line `(b) ^7[such number of officials, not exceeding five,] to be nominated by the State Government to represent that Government;`
  line
  line `(c) ^8[such number of persons, not exceeding five,] to be nominated by the State Government`
  line `from amongst the members of the local authorities functioning within the State;`
  line
  line `(d) ^9[such number of non-officials, not exceeding three,] to be nominated by the State`
  line `Government to represent the interests of agriculture, fishery or industry or trade or any other interest`
  line `which, in the opinion of the State Government, ought to be represented;`
  line
  line `(e) two persons to represent the companies or corporations owned, controlled or managed by the`
  line `State Government, to be nominated by that Government;`
  line
  line `^10 [(f) a full-time member-secretary, possessing qualifications, knowledge and experience of`
  line `scientific, engineering or management aspects of pollution control, to be appointed by the State`
  line Government.]
  line
  line `(3) Every State Board shall be a body corporate with the name specified by the State Government in`
  line `the notification under sub-section (1), having perpetual succession and a common seal with power,`
  line `subject to the provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract, and may, by`
  line `the said name, sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, no State Board shall be constituted for a`
  line `Union territory and in relation to a Union territory, the Central Board shall exercise the powers and`
  line `perform the functions of a State Board for that Union territory:`
  line
  line `Provided that in relation to any Union territory the Central Board may delegate all or any of its`
  line `powers and functions under this sub-section to such person or body of persons as the Central Government`
  line `may specify`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The brackets and words "(being a date not later than six months of the commencement of the Act in the State)"`
  line `omitted by Act 44 of 1978, s. 4 (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 4, for "State Board" (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  line
  line `3. The word "full-time" omitted by Act 44 of 1978, s. 4 (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 5 of 2024, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-2-2024).`
  line
  line `6. The proviso ins. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 4, (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "five officials" (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "five persons" (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "three non-officials" (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 4, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (4093)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Terms and conditions of service of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4093&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided by or under this`
  line `Act, a member of a Board, other than a member-secretary, shall hold office for a term of three years from`
  line `the date of his nomination:`
  line
  line `Provided that a member shall, notwithstanding the expiration of his term, continue to hold office until`
  line `his successor enters upon his office.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) The term of office of a member of a Board nominated under clause (b) or clause (e) of`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 3 or clause (b) or clause (e) of sub-section (2) of section 4 shall come to an end`
  line `as soon as he ceases to hold the office under the Central Government or the State Government or, as the`
  line `case may be, the company or corporation owned, controlled or managed by the Central Government or`
  line `the State Government, by virtue of which he was nominated.]`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government may, if it thinks fit, remove`
  line `any member of a Board before the expiry of his term of office, after giving him a reasonable opportunity`
  line `of showing cause against the same.`
  line
  line `(4) A member of a Board, other than the member-secretary, may at any time resign his office by`
  line `writing under his hand addressed--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of the chairman to the Central Government or, as the case may be, the`
  line `State Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) in any other case, to the chairman of the Board,`
  line
  line `and the seat of the chairman or such other member shall thereupon become vacant.`
  line
  line `(5) A member of a Board, other than the member-secretary, shall be deemed to have vacated his seat`
  line `if he is absent without reason, sufficient in the opinion of the Board, from three consecutive meetings of`
  line `the Board, ^2`
  line `[or where he is nominated under clause (c) or clause (e) of sub-section (2) of section 3 or`
  line `under clause (c) or clause (e) of sub-section (2) of section 4, if he ceases to be a member of the State`
  line `Board or of the local authority or, as the case may be, of the company or corporation owned, controlled or`
  line `managed by the Central Government or the State Government and such vacation of seat shall, in either`
  line `case, take effect from such date as the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify].`
  line
  line `(6) A casual vacancy in a Board shall be filled by a fresh nomination and the person nominated to fill`
  line `the vacancy shall hold office only for the remainder of the term for which the member in whose place he`
  line `was nominated.`
  line
  line `(7) A member of a Board ^3`
  line `[shall be eligible for renomination].`
  line
  line `(8) The other terms and conditions of service of a member of a Board, other than the chairman and`
  line `member-secretary, shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(9) The other terms and conditions of service of the chairman shall be such as may be prescribed ^4[by the Central Government].`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 5, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "certain words, brackets, letters and figures" (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 5, for "shall not be eligible for renomination for more than two terms" (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 5 of 2024, s. 3, (w.e.f. 15-2-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (4094)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title Disqualifications.
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4094&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall be a member of a Board, who--`
  line
  line `(a) is, or at any time has been adjudged insolvent or has suspended payment of his debts or has`
  line `compounded with his creditors, or`
  line
  line `(b) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court, or`
  line
  line `(c) is, or has been, convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government or, as`
  line `the case may be, of the State Government, involves moral turpitude, or`
  line
  line `(d) is, or at any time has been, convicted of an offence under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(e) has directly or indirectly by himself or by any partner, any share or interest in any firm or`
  line `company carrying on the business of manufacture, sale or hire of machinery, plant, equipment,`
  line `apparatus or fittings for the treatment of sewage or trade effluents, or`
  line
  line `(f) is a director or a secretary, manager or other salaried officer or employee of any company or`
  line `firm having any contract with the Board, or with the Government constituting the Board, or with a`
  line `local authority in the State, or with a company or corporation owned, controlled or managed by the`
  line `Government, for the carrying out of sewerage schemes or for the installation of plants for the`
  line `treatment of sewage or trade effluents, or`
  line
  line `(g) has so abused, in the opinion of the Central Government or as the case may be, of the State`
  line `Government, his position as a member, as to render his continuance on the Board detrimental to the`
  line `interest of the general public.`
  line
  line `(2) No order of removal shall be made by the Central Government or the State Government, as the`
  line `case may be, under this section unless the member concerned has been given a reasonable opportunity of`
  line `showing cause against the same.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-sections (1) and (7) of section 5, a member who has`
  line `been removed under this section shall not be eligible for renomination as a member.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (4095)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Vacation of seats by members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4095&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `If a member of a Board becomes subject to any of the`
  line `disqualifications specified in section 6, his seat shall become vacant.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (4096)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Meetings of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4096&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `A Board shall meet at least once in every three months and shall observe`
  line `such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that if, in the opinion of the chairman, any business of an urgent nature is to be transacted,`
  line `he may convene a meeting of the Board at such time as he thinks fit for the aforesaid purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (4097)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Constitution of committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4097&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may constitute as many committees consisting wholly`
  line `of members or wholly of other persons or partly of members and partly of other persons, and for such`
  line `purpose or purposes as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) A committee constituted under this section shall meet at such time and at such place, and shall`
  line `observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings, as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(3) The members of a committee (other than the members of the Board) shall be paid such fees and`
  line `allowances, for attending its meetings and for attending to any other work of the Board as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (4098)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Temporary association of persons with Board for particular purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 6 (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4098&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Board may`
  line `associate with itself in such manner, and for such purposes, as may be prescribed any person whose`
  line `assistance or advice it may desire to obtain in performing any of its functions under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A person associated with the Board under sub-section (1) for any purpose shall have a right to`
  line `take part in the discussions of the Board relevant to that purpose, but shall not have a right to vote at a`
  line `meeting of the Board, and shall not be a member for any other purpose.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(3) A person associated with the Board under sub-section (1) for any purpose shall be paid such fees`
  line `and allowances, for attending its meetings and for attending to any other work of the Board, as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (4099)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Vacancy in Board not to invalidate acts or proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4099&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of a Board or`
  line `any committee thereof shall be called in question on the ground merely of the existence of any vacancy`
  line `in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Board or such committee, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (4100)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 12
  title `Delegation of powers to Chairman.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4100&sectionno=11A&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[11A. Delegation of powers to Chairman.--The Chairman of a Board shall exercise such powers`
  line `and perform such duties as may be prescribed or as may, from time to time, be delegated to him by the`
  line Board.]
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (4101)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Member-secretary and officers and other employees of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4101&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The terms and conditions`
  line `of service of the member-secretary shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The member-secretary shall exercise such powers and perform such duties as may be prescribed`
  line `or as may, from time to time, be delegated to him by the Board or its chairman.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to such rules as may be made by the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State`
  line `Government in this behalf, a Board may appoint such officers and employees as it considers necessary for`
  line `the efficient performance of its functions ^1`
  line ***.
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(3A) The method of recruitment and the terms and conditions of service (including the scales of`
  line `pay) of the officers (other than the member-secretary) and other employees of the Central Board or a`
  line `State Board shall be such as may be determined by regulations made by the Central Board or, as the case`
  line `may be, by the State Board:`
  line
  line `Provided that no regulation made under this sub-section shall take effect unless,--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a regulation made by the Central Board, it is approved by the Central`
  line `Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a regulation made by a State Board, it is approved by the State Government.]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(3B) The Board may, by general or special order, and subject to such conditions and limitations, if`
  line `any, as may be specified in the order delegate to any officer of the Board such of its powers and functions`
  line `under this Act as it may deem necessary.]`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to such conditions as may be prescribed, a Board may from time to time appoint any`
  line `qualified person to be a consulting engineer to the Board and pay him such salaries and allowances and`
  line `subject him to such other terms and conditions of service as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Certain words omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 6 (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (4102)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Constitution of Joint Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4102&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, an agreement`
  line `may be entered into--`
  line
  line `(a) by two or more Governments of contiguous States, or`
  line
  line `(b) by the Central Government (in respect of one or more Union territories) and one or more`
  line `Governments of States contiguous to such Union territory or Union territories,`
  line
  line `to be in force for such period and to be subject to renewal for such further period, if any, as may be`
  line `specified in the agreement to provide for the constitution of a Joint Board,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case referred to in clause (a), for all the participating States, and`
  line
  line `(ii) in a case referred to in clause (b), for the participating Union territory or Union territories and`
  line `the State or States.`
  line
  line `(2) An agreement under this section may--`
  line
  line `(a) provide, in a case referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1), for the apportionment between`
  line `the participating States and in a case referred to in clause (b) of that sub-section, for the`
  line `apportionments between the Central Government and the participating State Government or State`
  line `Governments, of the expenditure in connection with the Joint Board;`
  line
  line `(b) determine, in a case referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1), which of the participating`
  line `State Governments and in a case referred to in clause (b) of that sub-section, whether the Central`
  line `Government or the participating State Government (if there are more than one participating State, also`
  line `which of the participating State Governments) shall exercise and perform the several powers and`
  line `functions of the State Government under this Act and the references in this Act to the State`
  line `Government shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(c) provide for consultation, in a case referred to in clause (a) of sub-section (1), between the`
  line `participating State Governments and in a case referred to in clause (b) of that sub-section, between the`
  line `Central Government and the participating State Government or State Governments either generally or`
  line `with reference to particular matters arising under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) make such incidental and ancillary provisions, not inconsistent with this Act, as may be`
  line `deemed necessary or expedient for giving effect to the agreement.`
  line
  line `(3) An agreement under this section shall be published, in a case referred to in clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (1), in the Official Gazette of the participating States and in a case referred to in cause (b) of`
  line `that sub-section, in the Official Gazette of the participating Union territory or Union territories and`
  line `participating State or States.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (4103)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Composition of Joint Boards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4103&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Joint Board constituted in pursuance of an agreement`
  line `entered into under clause (a) of sub-section (1) of section 13 shall consist of the following members,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a full-time chairman, being a person having special knowledge or practical experience in`
  line `respect of ^1`
  line `[matters relating to environmental protection] or a person having knowledge and`
  line `experience in administering institutions dealing with the matters aforesaid, to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) two officials from each of the participating States to be nominated by the concerned`
  line `participating State Government to represent that Government;`
  line
  line `(c) one person to be nominated by each of the participating State Governments from amongst`
  line `the members of the local authorities functioning within the State concerned;`
  line
  line `(d) one non-official to be nominated by each of the participating State Governments to represent`
  line `the interests of agriculture, fishery or industry or trade in the State concerned or any other interest`
  line `which, in the opinion of the participating State Government, is to be represented;`
  line
  line `(e) two persons to be nominated by the Central Government to represent the companies or`
  line `corporations owned, controlled or managed by the participating State Governments;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(f) a full-time member-secretary, possessing qualifications, knowledge and experience of`
  line `scientific, engineering or management aspects of pollution control, to be appointed by the`
  line `Central Government.]`
  line
  line `(2) A Joint Board constituted in pursuance of an agreement entered into under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 13 shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a full-time chairman, being a person having special knowledge or practical experience in`
  line `respect of ^3`
  line `[matters relating to environmental protection] or a person having knowledge and`
  line `experience in administering institutions dealing with the matters aforesaid, to be nominated by the`
  line `Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) two officials to be nominated by the Central Government from the participating Union`
  line `territory or each of the participating Union territories, as the case may be, and two officials to be`
  line `nominated, from the participating State or each of the participating States, as the case may be, by the`
  line `concerned participating State Government;`
  line
  line `(c) one person to be nominated by the Central Government from amongst the members of the`
  line `local authorities functioning within the participating Union territory or each of the participating Union`
  line `territories, as the case may be, and one person to be nominated, from amongst the members of the`
  line `local authorities functioning within the participating State or each of the participating States, as the`
  line `case may be, by the concerned participating State Government;`
  line
  line `(d) one non-official to be nominated by the Central Government and one person to be nominated`
  line `by the participating State Government or State Governments to represent the interests of agriculture,`
  line `fishery or industry or trade in the Union territory or in each of the Union territories or the State or in`
  line `each of the States, as the case may be, or any other interest which in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government or, as the case may be, of the State Government is to be represented;`
  line
  line `(e) two persons to be nominated by the Central Government to represent the companies or`
  line `corporations owned, controlled or managed by the Central Government and situate in the`
  line `participating Union territory or territories and two persons to be nominated by the Central`
  line `Government to represent the companies or corporations owned, controlled or managed by the`
  line `participating State Governments;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(f) a full-time member-secretary, possessing qualifications, knowledge and experience`
  line `of scientific, engineering or management aspects of pollution control, to be appointed by the Central`
  line Government.]
  line
  line `(3) When a Joint Board is constituted in pursuance of an agreement under clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 13, the provisions of sub-section (4) of section 4 shall cease to apply in relation`
  line `to the Union territory for which the Joint Board is constituted.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (3), the provisions of sub-section (3) of section 4 and`
  line `sections 5 to 12 (inclusive) shall apply in relation to the Joint Board and its member-secretary as they`
  line `apply in relation to a State Board and its member-secretary.`
  line
  line `(5) Any reference in this Act to the State Board shall, unless the context otherwise requires, be`
  line `construed as including a Joint Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 7, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 9, for certain words (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 7, for clause (f) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (4104)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Special provision relating to giving of directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4104&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this`
  line `Act where any Joint Board is constituted under section 13,--`
  line
  line `(a) the Government of the State for which the Joint Board is constituted shall be competent to`
  line `give any direction under this Act only in cases where such direction relates to a matter within the`
  line `exclusive territorial jurisdiction of the State;`
  line
  line `(b) the Central Government alone shall be competent to give any direction under this Act where`
  line `such direction relates to a matter within the territorial jurisdiction of two or more States or pertaining`
  line `to a Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (4105)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Functions of Central Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 8 (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4105&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the main function of the`
  line `Central Board shall be to promote cleanliness of streams and wells in different areas of the States.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing function, the Central Board`
  line `may perform all or any of the following functions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) advise the Central Government on any matter concerning the prevention and control of`
  line `water pollution;`
  line
  line `(b) co-ordinate the activities of the State Boards and resolve disputes among them;`
  line
  line `(c) provide technical assistance and guidance to the State Boards, carry out and sponsor`
  line `investigations and research relating to problems of water pollution and prevention, control or`
  line `abatement of water pollution;`
  line
  line `(d) plan and organise the training of persons engaged or to be engaged in programmes for the`
  line `prevention, control or abatement of water pollution on such terms and conditions as the Central Board`
  line `may specify;`
  line
  line `(e) organise through mass media a comprehensive programme regarding the prevention`
  line `and control of water pollution;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(ee) perform such of the functions of any State Board as may be specified in an order made`
  line `under sub- section (2) of section 18;]`
  line
  line `(f) collect, compile and publish technical and statistical data relating to water pollution and the`
  line `measures devised for its effective prevention and control and prepare manuals, codes or guides`
  line `relating to treatment and disposal of sewage and trade effluents and disseminate information`
  line `connected therewith;`
  line
  line `(g) lay down, modify or annul, in consultation with the State Government concerned,`
  line `the standards for a stream or well:`
  line
  line `Provided that different standards may be laid down for the same stream or well or for different`
  line `streams or wells, having regard to the quality of water, flow characteristics of the stream or well and`
  line `the nature of the use of the water in such stream or well or streams or wells;`
  line
  line `(h) plan and cause to be executed a nation-wide programme for the prevention, control`
  line `or abatement of water pollution;`
  line
  line `(i) perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board may establish or recognise a laboratory or laboratories to enable the Board to perform`
  line `its functions under this section efficiently including the analysis of samples of water from any stream or`
  line `well or of samples of any sewage or trade effluents.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (4106)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Functions of State Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4106&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the functions of a State`
  line `Board shall be--`
  line
  line `(a) to plan a comprehensive programme for the prevention, control or abatement of pollution of`
  line `streams and wells in the State and to secure the execution thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) to advise the State Government on any matter concerning the prevention, control or abatement`
  line `of water pollution;`
  line
  line `(c) to collect and disseminate information relating to water pollution and the prevention, control`
  line `or abatement thereof;`
  line
  line `(d) to encourage, conduct and participate investigations and research relating to problems of`
  line `water pollution and prevention, control or abatement of water pollution;`
  line
  line `(e) to collaborate with the Central Board in organising the training of persons engaged or to be`
  line `engaged in programmes relating, to prevention, control or abatement of water pollution and to`
  line `organise mass education programmes relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(f) to inspect sewage or trade effluents, works and plants for the treatment of sewage and trade`
  line `effluents and to review plans, specifications or other data relating to plants set up for the treatment of`
  line `water, works for the purification thereof and the system for the disposal of sewage or trade effluents`
  line `or in connection with the grant of any consent as required by this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) to lay down, modify or annul effluent standards for the sewage and trade effluents and for the`
  line `quality of receiving waters (not being water in an inter-State stream) resulting from the discharge of`
  line `effluents and to classify waters of the State;`
  line
  line `(h) to evolve economical and reliable methods of treatment of sewage and trade effluents, having`
  line `regard to the peculiar conditions of soils, climate and water resources of different regions and more`
  line `especially the prevailing flow characteristics of water in streams and wells which render it impossible`
  line `to attain even the minimum degree of dilution;`
  line
  line `(i) to evolve methods of utilisation of sewage and suitable trade effluents in agriculture;`
  line
  line `(j) to evolve efficient methods of disposal of sewage and trade effluents on land, as are necessary`
  line `on account of the predominant conditions of scant stream flows that do not provide for major part of`
  line `the year the minimum degree of dilution;`
  line
  line `(k) to lay down standards of treatment of sewage and trade effluents to be discharged into any`
  line `particular stream taking into account the minimum fair weather dilution available in that stream and`
  line `the tolerance limits of pollution permissible in the water of the stream, after the discharge of such`
  line effluents;
  line
  line `(l) to make, vary or revoke any order--`
  line
  line `(i) for the prevention, control or abatement of discharges of waste into streams or wells;`
  line
  line `(ii) requiring any person concerned to construct new systems for the disposal of sewage and`
  line `trade effluents or to modify, alter or extend any such existing system or to adopt such remedial`
  line `measures as are necessary to prevent, control or abate water pollution;`
  line
  line `(m) to lay down effluent standards to be complied with by persons while causing discharge of`
  line `sewage or sullage or both and to lay down, modify or annul effluent standards for the sewage and`
  line `trade effluents;`
  line
  line `(n) to advise the State Government with respect to the location of any industry the carrying on of`
  line `which is likely to pollute a stream or well;`
  line
  line `(o) to perform such other functions as may be prescribed or as may, from time to time, be`
  line `entrusted to it by the Central Board or the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may establish or recognise a laboratory or laboratories to enable the Board to perform`
  line `its functions under this section efficiently, including the analysis of samples of water from any stream or`
  line `well or of samples of any sewage or trade effluents.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (4107)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Powers to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4107&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] In the performance of its functions under this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Board shall be bound by such directions in writing as the Central Government may`
  line `give to it; and`
  line
  line `(b) every State Board shall be bound by such directions in writing as the Central Board or the`
  line `State Government may give to it:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a direction given by the State Government is inconsistent with the direction`
  line `given by the Central Board, the matter shall be referred to the Central Government for its decision.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Where the Central Government is of the opinion that any State Board has defaulted in`
  line `complying with any directions given by the Central Board under sub-section (1) and as a result of such`
  line `default a grave emergency has arisen and it is necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest, it`
  line `may, by order, direct the Central Board to perform any of the functions of the State Board in relation to`
  line `such area, for such period and for such purposes, as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the Central Board performs any of the functions of the State Board in pursuance of a`
  line `direction under sub-section (2), the expenses, if any, incurred by the Central Board with respect to the`
  line `performance of such functions may, if the State Board is empowered to recover such expenses, be`
  line `recovered by the Central Board with interest (at such reasonable rate as the Central Government may, by`
  line `order, fix) from the date when a demand for such expenses is made until it is paid from the person or`
  line `persons concerned as arrears of land revenue or of public demand.`
  line
  line `(4) For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that any directions to perform the functions of any`
  line `State Board given under sub-section (2) in respect of any area would not preclude the State Board from`
  line `performing such functions in any other area in the State or any of its other functions in that area.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. S. 18 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 53 of 1988, s. 9 (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 9 (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (4108)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power of State Government to restrict the application of the Act to certain areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4108&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, if the State Government, after consultation`
  line `with, or on the recommendation of, the State Board, is of opinion that the provisions of this Act need not`
  line `apply to the entire State, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, restrict the application of this Act`
  line `to such area or areas as may be declared therein as water pollution, prevention and control area or areas`
  line `and thereupon the provisions of this Act shall apply only to such area or areas.`
  line
  line `(2) Each water pollution, prevention and control area may be declared either by reference to a map or`
  line `by reference to the line of any watershed or the boundary of any district or partly by one method and`
  line `partly by another.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) alter any water pollution, prevention and control area whether by way of extension or`
  line `reduction; or`
  line
  line `(b) define a new water pollution, prevention and control area in which may be merged one or`
  line `more water pollution, prevention and control areas, or any part or parts thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (4109)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to obtain information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 10, for "industry or trade" (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4109&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of enabling a State Board to perform the`
  line `functions conferred on it by or under this Act, the State Board or any officer empowered by it in that`
  line `behalf, may make surveys of any area and gauge and keep records of the flow or volume and other`
  line `characteristics of any stream or well in such area, and may take steps for the measurement and recording`
  line `of the rainfall in such area or any part thereof and for the installation and maintenance for those purposes`
  line `of gauges or other apparatus and works connected therewith, and carry out stream surveys and may take`
  line `such other steps as may be necessary in order to obtain any information required for the purposes`
  line aforesaid.
  line
  line `(2) A State Board may give directions requiring any person who in its opinion is abstracting water`
  line `from any such stream or well in the area in quantities which are substantial in relation to the flow or`
  line `volume of that stream well or is discharging sewage or trade effluent into any such stream or well, to give`
  line `such information as to the abstraction or the discharge at such times and in such form as may be specified`
  line `in the directions.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (2), a State Board may, with a view to`
  line `preventing or controlling pollution of water, give directions requiring any person in charge of any`
  line `establishment where any ^1`
  line `[industry, operation or process, or treatment and disposal system] is carried on,`
  line `to furnish to it information regarding the construction, installation or operation of such establishment or`
  line `of any disposal system or of any extension or addition thereto in such establishment and such other`
  line `particulars as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (4110)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to take samples of effluents and procedure to be followed in connection therewith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 10, for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4110&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) A State Board or any officer empowered by it in this behalf shall have power to take for`
  line `the purpose of analysis samples of water from any stream or well or samples of any sewage or trade`
  line `effluent which is passing from any plant or vessel or from or over any place into any such stream or well.`
  line
  line `(2) The result of any analysis of a sample of any sewage or trade effluent taken under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall not be admissible in evidence in any legal proceeding unless the provisions of`
  line `sub-sections (3), (4) and (5) are complied with.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the provisions of sub-sections (4) and (5), when a sample (composite or otherwise as`
  line `may be warranted by the process used) of any sewage or trade effluent is taken for analysis under`
  line `sub-section (1), the person taking the sample shall--`
  line
  line `(a) serve on the person in charge of, or having control over, the plant or vessel or in occupation of`
  line `the place (which person is hereinafter referred to as the occupier) or any agent of such occupier, a`
  line `notice, then and there in such form as may be prescribed of his intention to have it so analysed;`
  line
  line `(b) in the presence of the occupier or his agent, divide the sample into two parts;`
  line
  line `(c) cause each part to be placed in a container which shall be marked and sealed and shall also be`
  line `signed both by the person taking the sample and the occupier or his agent;`
  line
  line `(d) send one container forthwith,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case where such sample is taken from any area situated in a Union territory, to the`
  line `laboratory established or recognised by the Central Board under section 16; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, to the laboratory established or recognised by the State Board under`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(e) on the request of the occupier or his agent, send the second container,--`
  line
  line `(i) in a case where such sample is taken from any area situated in a Union territory, to the`
  line `laboratory established or specified under sub-section (1) of section 51; and`
  line
  line `(ii) in any other case, to the laboratory established or specified under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 52.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(4) When a sample of any sewage or trade affluent is taken for analysis under sub-section (1) and`
  line `the person taking the sample serves on the occupier or his agent, a notice under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (3) and the occupier or his agent wilfully absents himself, then,--`
  line
  line `(a) the sample so taken shall be placed in a container which shall be marked and sealed and shall`
  line `also be signed by the person taking the sample and the same shall be sent forthwith by such person for`
  line `analysis to the laboratory referred to in sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (ii), as the case may be, of`
  line `clause (e) of sub-section (3) and such person shall inform the Government analyst appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), as the case may be, of section 53, in writing about the wilful`
  line `absence of the occupier or his agent; and`
  line
  line `(b) the cost incurred in getting such sample analysed shall be payable by the occupier or his agent`
  line `and in case of default of such payment, the same shall be recoverable from the occupier or his agent,`
  line `as the case may be, as an arrear of land revenue or of public demand:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such recovery shall be made unless the occupier or, as the case may be, his agent has`
  line `been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(5) When a sample of any sewage or trade effluent is taken for analysis under sub-section (1) and the`
  line `person taking the sample serves on the occupier or his agent a notice under clause (a) of sub-section (3)`
  line `and the occupier or his agent who is present at the time of taking the sample does not make a request for`
  line `dividing the sample into two parts as provided in clause (b) of sub-section (3), then, the sample so taken`
  line `shall be placed in a container which shall be marked and sealed and shall also be signed by the person`
  line `taking the sample and the same shall be sent forthwith by such person for analysis to the laboratory`
  line `referred to in sub-clause (i) or sub-clause (ii), as the case may be, of clause (d) of sub-section (3).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (4111)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Reports of the result of analysis on samples taken under section 21.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4111&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a sample of`
  line `any sewage or trade effluent has been sent for analysis to the laboratory established or recognised by the`
  line `Central Board or, as the case may be, the State Board, the concerned Board analyst appointed under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 53 shall analyse the sample and submit a report in the prescribed form of the`
  line `result of such analysis in triplicate to the Central Board or the State Board, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the report under sub-section (1), one copy of the report shall be sent by the`
  line `Central Board or the State Board, as the case may be, to the occupier or his agent referred to in section 21,`
  line `another copy shall be preserved for production before the court in case any legal proceedings are taken`
  line `against him and the other copy shall be kept by the concerned Board.`
  line
  line `(3) Where a sample has been sent for analysis under clause (e) of sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) of`
  line `section 21 to any laboratory mentioned therein, the Government analyst referred to in that sub-section`
  line `shall analyse the sample and submit a report in the prescribed form of the result of the analysis in`
  line `triplicate to the Central Board or, as the case may be, the State Board which shall comply with the`
  line `provisions of sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) If there is any inconsistency or discrepancy between, or variation in the results of, the analysis`
  line `carried out by the laboratory established or recognised by the Central Board or the State Board, as the`
  line `case may be, and that of the laboratory established or specified under section 51 or section 52, as the case`
  line `may be, the report of the latter shall prevail.`
  line
  line `(5) Any cost incurred in getting any sample analysed at the request of the occupier or his agent shall`
  line `be payable by such occupier or his agent and in case of default the same shall be recoverable from him as`
  line `arrears of land revenue or of public demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (4112)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power of entry and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4112&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this section, any person`
  line `empowered by a State Board in this behalf shall have a right at any time to enter, with such assistance as`
  line `he considers necessary, any place--`
  line
  line `(a) for the purpose of performing any of the functions of the Board entrusted to him;`
  line
  line `(b) for the purpose of determining whether and if so in what manner, any such functions are to be`
  line `performed or whether any provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder of any notice, order,`
  line `direction or authorisation served, made, given, or granted under this Act is being or has been`
  line `complied with;`
  line
  line `(c) for the purpose of examining any plant, record, register, document or any other material object`
  line `or for conducting a search of any place in which he has reason to believe that an offence under this`
  line `Act or the rules made thereunder has been or is being or is about to be committed and for seizing any`
  line `such plant, record, register, document or other material object, if he has reason to believe that it may`
  line `furnish evidence of the commission of an offence punishable under this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that the right to enter under this sub-section for the inspection of a well shall be exercised`
  line `only at reasonable hours in a case where such well is situated in any premises used for residential`
  line `purposes and the water thereof is used exclusively for domestic purposes.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of ^1`
  line `[the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974)], or, in relation to the State`
  line `of Jammu and Kashmir*, the provisions of any corresponding law in force in that State, shall, so far as may`
  line `be, apply to any search or seizure under this section as they apply to any search or seizure made under the`
  line `authority of a warrant issued under ^2`
  line `[section 94] of the said Code, or, as the case may be, under the`
  line `corresponding provisions of the said law.`
  line
  line `Explanation. -- For the purposes of this section, place includes vessel.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 11, for "the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898)"(w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "section 98" (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (4113)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Prohibition on use of stream or well for disposal of polluting matter, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1.Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 11, for "stream or well" (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4113&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) no person shall knowingly cause or permit any poisonous, noxious or polluting matter`
  line `determined in accordance with such standards as may be laid down by the State Board to enter`
  line `(whether directly or indirectly) into any ^1`
  line `[stream or well or sewer or on land]; or`
  line
  line `(b) no person shall knowingly cause or permit to enter into any stream any other matter which`
  line `may tend, either directly or in combination with similar matters, to impede the proper flow of the`
  line `water of the stream in a manner leading or likely to lead to a substantial aggravation of pollution due`
  line `to other causes or of its consequences.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be guilty of an offence under sub-section (1), by reason only of having done or`
  line `caused to be done any of the following acts, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) constructing, improving or maintaining in or across or on the bank or bed of any stream any`
  line `building, bridge, weir, dam, sluice, dock, pier, drain or sewer or other permanent works which he has`
  line `a right to construct, improve or maintain;`
  line
  line `(b) depositing any materials on the bank or in the bed of any stream for the purpose of reclaiming`
  line `land or for supporting, repairing or protecting the bank or bed of such stream provided such materials`
  line `are not capable of polluting such stream;`
  line
  line `(c) putting into any stream any sand or gravel or other natural deposit which has flowed from or`
  line `been deposited by the current of such stream;`
  line
  line `(d) causing or permitting, with the consent of the State Board, the deposit accumulated in a well,`
  line `pond or reservoir to enter into any stream.`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, after consultation with, or on the recommendation of, the`
  line `State Board, exempt, by notification in the Official Gazette, any person from the operation of`
  line `sub-section (1) subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification and any condition`
  line `so specified may by a like notification be altered, varied or amended.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (4114)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Restrictions on new outlets and new discharges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4114&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Subject to the provisions of this section,`
  line `no person shall, without the previous consent of the State Board,--`
  line
  line `(a) establish or take any steps to establish any industry, operation or process, or any treatment and`
  line `disposal system or any extension or addition thereto, which is likely to discharge sewage or trade`
  line `effluent into a stream or well or sewer or on land (such discharge being hereafter in this section`
  line `referred to as discharge of sewage); or`
  line
  line `(b) bring into use any new or altered outlet for the discharge of sewage; or`
  line
  line `(c) begin to make any new discharge of sewage:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the Central Government may in consultation with the Central Board, by notification in the Official Gazette, exempt certain categories of industrial plants from the provisions of this sub-section.]`
  line
  line `(2) An application for consent of the State Board under sub-section (1) shall be made in such form, contain such particulars and shall be accompanied by such fees as may be prescribed.]`
  line
  line `(3) The State Board may make such inquiry as it may deem fit in respect of the application for`
  line `consent referred to in sub-section (1) and in making any such inquiry shall follow such procedure as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(4) The State Board may--`
  line
  line `(a) grant its consent referred to in sub-section (1), subject to such conditions as it may impose,`
  line being--
  line
  line `(i) in cases referred to in clauses (a) and (b) of sub-section (1) of section 25, conditions as to the point of discharge of sewage or as to the use of that outlet or any other outlet for discharge of`
  line sewage;
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a new discharge, conditions as to the nature and composition, temperature,`
  line `volume or rate of discharge of the effluent from the land or premises from which the discharge or`
  line `new discharge is to be made; and`
  line
  line `(iii) that the consent will be valid only for such period as may be specified in the order,`
  line
  line `and any such conditions imposed shall be binding on any person establishing or taking any steps to`
  line `establish any industry, operation or process, or treatment and disposal system of extension or addition`
  line `thereto, or using the new or altered outlet, or discharging the effluent from the land or premises`
  line `aforesaid; or`
  line
  line `(b) refuse such consent for reasons to be recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `(5) Where, without the consent of the State Board, any industry, operation or process, or any`
  line `treatment and disposal system or any extension or addition thereto, is established, or any steps for such`
  line `establishment have been taken or a new or altered outlet is brought into use for the discharge of sewage or a new discharge of sewage is made, the State Board may serve on the person who has established or taken steps to establish any industry, operation or process, or any treatment and disposal system or any`
  line `extension or addition thereto, or using the outlet, or making the discharge, as the case may be, a notice`
  line `imposing any such conditions as it might have imposed on an application for its consent in respect of such`
  line `establishment, such outlet or discharge.`
  line
  line `(6) Every State Board shall maintain a register containing particulars of the conditions imposed under`
  line `this section and so much of the register as relates to any outlet, or to any effluent, from any land or`
  line `premises shall be open to inspection at all reasonable hours by any person interested in, or affected by`
  line `such outlet, land or premises, as the case may be, or by any person authorised by him in this behalf and`
  line `the conditions so contained in such register shall be conclusive proof that the consent was granted subject`
  line `to such conditions.]`
  line
  line `(7) The consent referred to in sub-section (1) shall, unless given or refused earlier, be deemed to have been given unconditionally on the expiry of a period of four months of the making of an application in this behalf complete in all respects to the State Board.`
  line
  line `(8) For the purposes of this section and sections 27 and 30,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "new or altered outlet" means any outlet which is wholly or partly constructed`
  line `on or after the commencement of this Act or which (whether so constructed or not) is substantially`
  line `altered after such commencement;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "new discharge" means a discharge which is not, as respects to nature and`
  line `composition, temperature, volume, and rate of discharge of the effluent substantially a continuation of`
  line `a discharge made within the preceding twelve months (whether by the same or a different outlet), so however that a discharge which is in other respects a continuation of previous discharge made as`
  line `aforesaid shall not be deemed to be a new discharge by reason of any reduction of the temperature or`
  line `volume or rate of discharge of the effluent as compared with the previous discharge.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 12, for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 5 of 2024, s. 4, for the proviso (w.e.f. 15-2-2024).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 12, for sub-sections (4), (5) and (6) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (4115)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Provision regarding existing discharge of sewage or trade effluent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4115&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Where immediately`
  line `before the commencement of this Act any person was discharging any sewage or trade effluent into`
  line a
  line ^1
  line `[stream or well or sewer or on land], the provisions of section 25 shall, so far as may be, apply in`
  line `relation to such person as they apply in relation to the person referred to in that section subject to the`
  line `modification that the application for consent to be made under sub-section (2) of that section ^2`
  line `[shall be`
  line `made on or before such date as may be specified by the State Government by notification in this behalf in`
  line `the Official Gazette].`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 13, for "stream or well" (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for certain words (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (4116)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Refusal or withdrawal of consent by State Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4116&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) A State Board shall not grant its`
  line `consent under sub-section (4) of section 25 for the establishment of any industry, operation or process, or`
  line `treatment and disposal system or extension or addition thereto, or to the bringing into use of a new or`
  line `altered outlet unless the industry, operation or process, or treatment and disposal system or extension or`
  line `addition thereto, or the outlet is so established as to comply with any conditions imposed by the Board to`
  line `enable it to exercise its right to take samples of the effluent.]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) A State Board may from time to time review--`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(a) any condition imposed under section 25 or section 26 and may serve on the person to whom`
  line `a consent under section 25 or section 26 is granted a notice making any reasonable variation of or`
  line `revoking any such condition;]`
  line
  line `(b) the refusal of any consent referred to in sub-section (1) of section 25 or section 26 or the grant`
  line `of such consent without any condition, and may make such orders as it deemed fit.]`
  line
  line `(3) Any condition imposed under section 25 or section 26 shall be subject to any variation made`
  line `under sub-section (2) and shall continue in force until revoked under that sub-section.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 13, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 14, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 13, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_a:
  sectionId (83514)
  sectionNo 27A
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to issue guidelines.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 5 of 2024, s. 5, (w.e.f. 15-2-2024)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=83514&sectionno=27A&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[27A. Power to issue guidelines.--(1) Notwithstanding anything in this Act, the Central Government in consultation with the Central Board, may, by notification in the Official Gazette, issue guidelines on the matters relating to the grant, refusal or cancellation of consent by any State Board for establishment of any industry, operation or process, or treatment and disposal system or to bringing into use of a new or altered outlet including the mechanism for time-bound disposal of the application made under section 25 or period of validity of such consent.`
  line
  line `(2) Every State Board, in discharge of its functions for the purposes of grant, refusal or cancellation of`
  line `consent under section 25 or section 27 shall act in accordance with the guidelines issued under sub-section (1).]`
  line
  line ^
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (4117)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 15, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4117&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an order made by the State Board under section 25,`
  line `section 26 or section 27 may, within thirty days from the date on which the order is communicated to him,`
  line `prefer an appeal to such authority (hereinafter referred to as the appellate authority) as the State`
  line `Government may think fit to constitute:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period of`
  line `thirty days if such authority is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the`
  line `appeal in time.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2) An appellate authority shall consist of a single person or three persons, as the State Government`
  line `may think fit, to be appointed by that Government.]`
  line
  line `(3) The form and manner in which an appeal may be preferred under sub-section (1), the fees payable`
  line `for such appeal and the procedure to be followed by the appellate authority shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `(4) On receipt of an appeal preferred under sub-section (1), the appellate authority shall, after giving`
  line `the appellant and the State Board an opportunity of being heard, dispose of the appeal as expeditiously as`
  line possible.
  line
  line `(5) If the appellate authority determines that any condition imposed, or the variation of any condition,`
  line `as the case may be, was unreasonable, then,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the appeal is in respect of the unreasonableness of any condition imposed, such`
  line `authority may direct either that the condition shall be treated as annulled or that there shall be`
  line `substituted for it such condition as appears to it to be reasonable;`
  line
  line `(b) where the appeal is in respect of the unreasonableness of any variation of a condition, such`
  line `authority may direct either that the condition shall be treated as continuing in force unvaried or that it`
  line `shall be varied in such manner as appears to it to be reasonable.`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (4118)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 31
  title Revision.
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4118&sectionno=29&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may at any time either of its own motion or on an`
  line `application made to it in this behalf, call for the records of any case where an order has been made by the`
  line `State Board under section 25, section 26 or section 27 for the purpose of satisfying itself as to the legality`
  line `or propriety of any such order and may pass such order in relation thereto as it may think it:`
  line
  line `Provided that the State Government shall not pass any order under this sub-section without affording`
  line `the State Board and the person who may be affected by such order a reasonable opportunity of being`
  line `heard in the matter.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall not revise any order made under section 25, section 26 or section 27`
  line `where an appeal against that order lies to the appellate authority, but has not been preferred or where an`
  line `appeal has been preferred such appeal is pending before the appellate authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (4119)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power of State Board to carry out certain works.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 14, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4119&sectionno=30&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1) Where under this Act, any conditions`
  line `have been imposed on any person while granting consent under section 25 or section 26 and such`
  line `conditions require such person to execute any work in connection therewith and such work has not been`
  line `executed within such time as may be specified in this behalf, the State Board may serve on the person`
  line `concerned a notice requiring him within such time (not being less than thirty days) as may be specified in`
  line `the notice to execute the work specified therein.]`
  line
  line `(2) If the person concerned fails to execute the work as required in the notice referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), then, after the expiration of the time specified in the said notice, the State Board may`
  line `itself execute or cause to be executed such work.`
  line
  line `(3) All expenses incurred by the State Board for the execution of the aforesaid work, together with`
  line `interest, at such rate as the State Government may, by order, fix, from the date when a demand for the`
  line `expenses is made until it is paid, may be recovered by that Board from the person concerned, as arrears of`
  line `land revenue, or of public demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (4120)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 33
  title `Furnishing of information to State Board and other agencies in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4120&sectionno=31&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) If at any`
  line `place where any industry, operation or process, or any treatment and disposal system or any extension or`
  line `addition thereto is being carried on, due to accident or other unforeseen act or event, any poisonous,`
  line `noxious or polluting matter is being discharged, or is likely to be discharged into a stream or well or`
  line `sewer or on land and, as a result of such discharge, the water in any stream or well is being polluted, or is`
  line `likely to be polluted, then the person incharge of such place shall forthwith intimate the occurrence of`
  line `such accident, act or event to the State Board and such other authorities or agencies as may be`
  line prescribed.]
  line
  line `(2) Where any local authority operates any sewerage system or sewage works, the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (1) shall apply to such local authority as they apply in relation to the person in charge of the`
  line `place where any industry or trade is being carried on.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (4121)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 34
  title `Emergency measures in case of pollution of stream or well.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4121&sectionno=32&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where it appears to the`
  line `State Board that any poisonous, noxious or polluting matter is present in ^1`
  line `[any stream or well or on land`
  line `by reason of the discharge of such matter in such stream or well or on such land] or has entered into that`
  line `stream or well due to any accident or other unforeseen act or event, and if the Board is of opinion that it is`
  line `necessary or expedient to take immediate action, it may for reasons to be recorded in writing, carry out`
  line `such operations as it may consider necessary for all or any of the following purposes, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(a) removing that matter from the ^2`
  line `[stream or well or on land] and disposing it of in such manner`
  line `as the Board considers appropriate;`
  line
  line `(b) remedying or mitigating any pollution caused by its presence in the stream or well;`
  line
  line `(c) issuing orders immediately restraining or prohibiting the person concerned from discharging`
  line `any poisonous, noxious or polluting matter ^3`
  line `[into the stream or well or on land], or from making`
  line `insanitary use of the stream or well.`
  line
  line `(2) The power conferred by sub-section (1) does not include the power to construct any works other`
  line `than works of a temporary character which are removed on or before the completion of the operations.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 16, for "any stream or well" (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for "stream or well" (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for "into the stream or well" (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (4122)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power of Board to make application to courts for restraining apprehended pollution of water in streams or wells.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 17, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4122&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Where it is apprehended by a Board that the water in any stream or`
  line `well is likely to be polluted by reason of the disposal or likely disposal of any matter in such stream or`
  line `well or in any sewer or on any land, or otherwise, the Board may make an application to a court, not`
  line `inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class, for restraining the`
  line `person who is likely to cause such pollution from so causing.]`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of an application under sub-section (1) the court may make such order as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Where under sub-section (2) the court makes an order restraining any person from polluting the`
  line `water in any stream or well, it may in that order--`
  line
  line `(i) direct the person who is likely to cause or has caused the pollution of the water in the stream or`
  line `well, to desist from taking such action as is likely to cause pollution or, as the case may be, to remove`
  line `from such stream or well, such matter, and`
  line
  line `(ii) authorise the Board, if the direction under clause (i) (being a direction for the removal of any`
  line `matter from such stream or well) is not complied with by the person to whom such direction is issued,`
  line `to undertake the removal and disposal of the matter in such manner as may be specified by the court.`
  line
  line `(4) All expenses incurred by the Board in removing any matter in pursuance of the authorisation`
  line `under clause (ii) of sub-section (3) or in the disposal of any such matter may be defrayed out of any`
  line `money obtained by the Board from such disposal and any balance outstanding shall be recoverable from`
  line `the person concerned as arrears of land revenue or of public demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_a:
  sectionId (4123)
  sectionNo 33A
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to give directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4123&sectionno=33A&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_33_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[33A. Power to give directions.--Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, but subject`
  line `to the provisions of this Act, and to any directions that the Central Government may give in this behalf, a`
  line `Board may, in the exercise of its powers and performance of its functions under this Act, issue any`
  line `directions in writing to any person, officer or authority, and such person, officer or authority shall be`
  line `bound to comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the avoidance of doubts, it is hereby declared that the power to issue directions`
  line `under this section includes the power to direct--`
  line
  line `(a) the closure, prohibition or regulation of any industry, operation or process; or`
  line
  line `(b) the stoppage or regulation of supply of electricity, water or any other service.]`
obj_root_law_sections_33_b:
  sectionId (57339)
  sectionNo 33B
  orderNo 37
  title `Appeal to National Green Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 19 of 2010, s. 36 and Schedule III (w.e.f. 18-10-2010).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=57339&sectionno=33B&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_33_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[33B. Appeal to National Green Tribunal.—Any person aggrieved by,—`
  line
  line `(a) an order or decision of the appellate authority under section 28, made on or after the commencement of`
  line `the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010; or`
  line
  line `(b) an order passed by the State Government under section 29, on or after the commencement of the`
  line `National Green Tribunal Act, 2010; or`
  line
  line `(c) directors issued under section 33A by a Board, on or after the commencement of the National Green`
  line `Tribunal Act, 2010,`
  line
  line `may file an appeal to the National Green Tribunal established under section 3 of the National Green Tribunal Act,`
  line `2010, in accordance with the provisions of that Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (4124)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 38
  title `Contributions by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4124&sectionno=34&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation`
  line `made by Parliament by law in this behalf, make in each financial year such contributions to the Central`
  line `Board as it may think necessary to enable the Board to perform its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (4125)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 39
  title `Contributions by State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4125&sectionno=35&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, after due appropriation`
  line `made by the Legislature of the State by law in this behalf, make in each financial year such contributions`
  line `to the State Board as it may think necessary to enable that Board to perform its functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (4126)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 40
  title `Fund of Central Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 44 of 1978, s. 16 (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4126&sectionno=36&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Board shall have its own fund, and all sums which`
  line `may, from time to time, be paid to it by the Central Government and all other receipts (by way of gifts,`
  line `grants, donations, benefactions ^1`
  line `[, fees] or otherwise) of that Board shall be carried to the fund of the`
  line `Board and all payments by the Board shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Board may expend such sums as it thinks fit for performing its functions under this`
  line `Act, ^1`
  line `[and, where any law for the time being in force relating to the prevention, control or abatement of`
  line `air pollution provides for the performance of any function under such law] by the Central Board, also for`
  line `performing its functions under such law and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the`
  line `fund of the Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (4127)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 41
  title `Fund of State Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 17, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-12-1978).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4127&sectionno=37&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Board shall have its own fund, and the sums which may,`
  line `from time to time, be paid to it by the State Government and all other receipts (by way of gifts, grants,`
  line `donations, benefactions ^1[,fees] or otherwise) of that Board shall be carried to the fund of the Board and`
  line `all payments by the Board shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Board may expend such sums as it thinks fit for performing its functions under this Act, ^1[and, where any law for the time being in force relating to the prevention, control or abatement of air`
  line `pollution provides for the performance of any function under such law] by the State Board, also for`
  line `performing its functions under such law and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the`
  line `fund of that Board.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_a:
  sectionId (4128)
  sectionNo 37A
  orderNo 42
  title `Borrowing powers of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 53 of 1988, s. 19 (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4128&sectionno=37A&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_37_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[37A. Borrowing powers of Board.--A Board may, with the consent of, or in accordance with, the`
  line `terms of any general or special authority given to it by the Central Government or, as the case may be, the`
  line `State Government, borrow money from any source by way of loans or issue of bonds, debentures or such`
  line `other instruments, as it may deem fit, for the performance of all or any of its functions under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (4129)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 43
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4129&sectionno=38&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `The Central Board or, as the case may be, the State Board shall, during each financial`
  line `year, prepare, in such form and at such time as may be prescribed, a budget in respect of the financial year`
  line `next ensuing showing the estimated receipt and expenditure, and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the`
  line `Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (4130)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 44
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for section 39 (w.e.f. 29-9-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4130&sectionno=39&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[39. Annual report.--(1) The Central Board shall, during each financial year, prepare, in such form`
  line `as may be prescribed, an annual report giving full account of its activities under this Act during the`
  line `previous financial year and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government within four`
  line `months from the last date of the previous financial year and that Government shall cause every such`
  line `report to be laid before both Houses of Parliament within nine months from the last date of the previous`
  line `financial year.`
  line
  line `(2) Every State Board shall, during each financial year, prepare, in such form as may be prescribed,`
  line `an annual report giving full account of its activities under this Act during the previous financial year and`
  line `copies thereof shall be forwarded to the State Government within four months from the last date of the`
  line `previous financial year and that Government shall cause every such report to be laid before the State`
  line `Legislature within a period of nine months from the last date of the previous financial year.]`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (4131)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 45
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4131&sectionno=40&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Board shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the Central`
  line `Government or, as the case may be, the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Board shall be audited by an auditor duly qualified to act as an auditor of`
  line `companies under section 226 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
  line
  line `(3) The said auditor shall be appointed by the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State`
  line `Government on the advice of the Comptroller and Auditor General of India.`
  line
  line `(4) Every auditor appointed to audit the accounts of the Board under this Act shall have the right to`
  line `demand the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to`
  line `inspect any of the offices of the Board.`
  line
  line `(5) Every such auditor shall send a copy of his report together with an audited copy of the accounts to`
  line `the Central Government or, as the case may be, the State Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government shall, as soon as may be after the receipt of the audit report under`
  line `sub-section (5), cause the same to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(7) The State Government shall, as soon as may be after the receipt of the audit report under`
  line `sub-section (5), cause the same to be laid before the State Legislature.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (4132)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 46
  title `Failure to comply provisions of section 20 or directions issued thereunder.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2024, s. 6, for section 41, (w.e.f. 15-2-2024)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4132&sectionno=41&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `^1[41. Failure to comply with provisions of section 20 or directions issued thereunder.--(1) Whoever contravenes or does not comply with the directions given under sub-section (2) or sub-section (3) of section 20, within such time as may be specified in the direction, shall, in respect of each such contravention or non-compliance, be liable to pay a penalty which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees, but which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person continues contravention or non-compliance under sub-section (1), he shall be`
  line `liable to pay an additional penalty of ten thousand rupees every day during which such contravention continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_41_a:
  sectionId (92417)
  sectionNo 41A
  orderNo 47
  title `Failure to comply with provisions of section 32, or directions issued under section 33 or section 33A.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2024, s. 6, for section 41, (w.e.f. 15-2-2024)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=92417&sectionno=41A&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_41_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[41A. Failure to comply with provisions of section 32, or directions issued under section 33 or section 33A--(1) Whoever contravenes or does not comply with any order or direction issued under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 32 or any direction issued by a court under sub-section (2) of section 33 or any direction issued under section 33A, shall, in respect of each such contravention or noncompliance, be liable to pay the penalty which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees, but which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person continues contravention or non-compliance under sub-section (1), he shall be liable to pay an additional penalty of ten thousand rupees every day during which such contravention continues.]`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (4133)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 48
  title `Penalty for certain acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4133&sectionno=42&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(a) destroys, pulls down, removes, injures or defaces any pillar, post or stake fixed in the ground`
  line `or any notice or other matter put up, inscribed or placed, by or under the authority of the Board, or`
  line
  line `(b) obstructs any person acting under the orders or directions of the Board from exercising his`
  line `powers and performing his functions under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(c) damages any works or property belonging to the Board, or`
  line
  line `(d) fails to furnish to any officer or other employee of the Board any information required by him`
  line `for the purpose of this Act, or`
  line
  line `(e) fails to intimate the occurrence of any accident or other unforeseen act or event under`
  line `section 31 to the Board and other authorities or agencies as required by that section, or`
  line
  line `(f) in giving any information which he is required to give under this Act, knowingly or wilfully`
  line `makes a statement which is false in any material particular, or`
  line
  line `(g) for the purpose of obtaining any consent under section 25 or section 26, knowingly or wilfully makes a statement which is false in any material particular,`
  line
  line `^1[shall be liable to pay penalty which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees, but which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees.]`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Where any person continues contravention or non-compliance under sub-section (1), he shall be liable to pay an additional penalty of ten thousand rupees every day during which such contravention continues.].`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2021, s. 7, for long line (w.e.f. 15-2-2024).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 15-2-2024).`
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (4134)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 49
  title `Penalty for contravention of provisions of section 24.`
  content `^1[43. Penalty for contravention of provisions of section 24.— Whoever contravenes the provisions of section 24, shall be liable to pay the penalty which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees, but which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees and where such contravention continues, he shall be liable to pay an additional penalty of ten thousand rupees every day during which such contravention continues.[`
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 5 of 2021, s. 8, for section 43 and 44 (w.e.f. 15-2-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4134&sectionno=43&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (4135)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 50
  title `Penalty for contravention of section 25 or section 26.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 2024, s. 8, for section 43 and 44 (w.e.f. 15-2-2024).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722&sectionId=4135&sectionno=44&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00003_197606_1517807320722
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `^1[Where for the purpose of grant of a`
  line `consent in pursuance of the provisions of section 25 or section 26, the use of a meter or gauge or other`
  line `measure or monitoring device is required and such device is used for the purposes of those provisions, any`
  line `person who knowingly or wilfully alters or interferes with that device so as to prevent it from monitoring`
  line `or measuring correctly shall be liable to pay penalty which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees, but`
  line `which may extend to fifteen lakh rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (4136)
